# Quality Assurance

## Code Quality Checklist

### Backend (Python)
- [ ] Follows PEP 8 style guide
- [ ] Type hints where appropriate
- [ ] Comprehensive docstrings
- [ ] Proper error handling
- [ ] Unit tests written
- [ ] No linting errors

### Frontend (TypeScript/React)
- [ ] Follows ESLint configuration
- [ ] Strict type checking enabled
- [ ] Component structure maintained
- [ ] Proper error handling
- [ ] Unit tests written
- [ ] No TypeScript errors

## Testing Requirements

- All modules must have unit tests (both frontend and backend)
- Test coverage should be comprehensive
- Integration tests for end-to-end flow
- Backend: Run tests before committing: `pytest tests/`
- Frontend: Run tests before committing: `npm test`

## Documentation Quality

- README.md must match actual implementation
- Usage guides must be accurate
- Code comments explain complex logic
- Configuration options documented
